Charges have been unsealed against husband and wife owners of an Orlando health care clinic for their roles in a fraud scheme that resulted in the submission of more than $3 million in allegedly fraudulent claims to Medicare.</dd> 

<dt id="CEA2014120403">December 3, 2014; U.S. Attorney; Southern District of New York</dt>
